The Busia county assembly has passed seven bills related to agriculture.Speaker Bernard Wamalwa said on Tuesday that this brings to 51 the number of bills the assembly has passed since functions were devolved in 2013.Wamalwa spoke on the first day of the Lake Region Agribusiness Summit and Expo Conference at Busia Agricultural Training College.He said the Agriculture bills include the Agricultural Development and Co-operative Development Funds and Busia County Trade Revolving Fund bills.He said the assembly passed the bills to enable farmers get affordable loans. The speaker said the assembly passed the County Decentralised Bill, that introduced recruitment of 119 village administrators. Wamalwa said the Investment Bill will be key, especially in improving agribusiness.